2026-06-09 14:42:37,741 DEBUG Tool call: submit_final_result({'final_result': '## Annualized Q1 2026 Run-Rate vs. FY2025\n\n**Consolidated Revenue:**\n- Q1 2026: $4,694M → Annualized: $18,776M vs. FY2025: $18,674M → **Implied growth: +0.55%** (essentially flat)\n\n**Connectivity Revenue:**\n- Q1 2026: $3,257M → Annualized: $13,028M vs. FY2025: $11,387M → **Implied growth: +14.41%**\n\n**Non-Connectivity (Space + AI combined):**\n- Q1 2026: $1,437M → Annualized: $5,748M vs. FY2025: $7,287M → **Implied growth: −21.12%**\n\n**Segment Detail:**\n- Space: $619M annualized to $2,476M vs. FY2025 $4,086M → **−39.4%**\n- AI (xAI/X): $818M annualized to $3,272M vs. FY2025 $3,201M → **+2.2%**\n\n**Revenue Mix Shift:** Connectivity\'s share rose from 61.0% (FY2025) to 69.4% (Q1 2026), an +8.4 pp increase.\n\n**YoY Q1 Comparison:** Consolidated Q1 revenue grew +15.4% ($4,067M → $4,694M), but Connectivity Q1 grew +31.6% ($2,475M → $3,257M), confirming Connectivity is outpacing the consolidated entity.\n\n**What This Suggests About Concentration of Momentum:**\nAll consolidated revenue momentum is concentrated in Connectivity (Starlink). Connectivity is adding ~$1.6B in annualized incremental revenue, while Space and AI combined are shedding ~$1.5B. The headline +0.55% consolidated growth is an illusion of stability—it masks a sharp contraction in the legacy Space segment (−39.4%) and stagnation in the AI segment (+2.2%). Connectivity is not merely the primary growth driver; it is the *sole* growth driver, contributing 100%+ of net momentum. This creates significant concentration risk: any deceleration in Starlink subscriber or ARPU growth would immediately expose the consolidated top line to the headwinds in the other two segments.\n\n*Note: All figures reflect the retrospectively recast consolidated entity (including xAI and X Holdings) for all periods presented. Q1 annualization assumes linear seasonality.*\n\n{\n  "sources": [\n    {\n      "url": "https://www.sec.gov/Archives/edgar/data/1181412/000162828026036936/spaceexplorationtechnologi.htm",\n      "name": "SpaceX S-1 Filing (May 20, 2026) — SEC EDGAR"\n    }\n  ]\n}'})
